WEBVTT

00:00.533 --> 00:03.053
Hey, I've gained a lot
of ground in the polls. That's good news.

00:03.082 --> 00:04.895
Yeah, I have you down
only four points,

00:05.015 --> 00:06.816
but they're running a ton
of new negative ads.

00:06.885 --> 00:08.433
Maybe you should fight back.

00:08.467 --> 00:09.768
Ben, your heart's
in the right place.

00:09.802 --> 00:11.102
Your heart and your butt.

00:11.137 --> 00:12.621
I will not go negative.

00:12.655 --> 00:13.905
Crap on a turd!

00:13.939 --> 00:16.041
Care for a "Recall Knope"
gift bag?

00:16.075 --> 00:18.610
The committee to recall
Leslie Knope is relentless.

00:18.644 --> 00:21.163
Look what they're handing out
at elementary schools.

00:21.214 --> 00:22.614
[Recorded voice]
I'm Leslie Knope.

00:22.632 --> 00:23.832
Tell your parents to recall me.

00:23.850 --> 00:31.573
[Extensive flatulence]

00:31.607 --> 00:33.758
We all know that I cannot
spend as much money on ads

00:33.793 --> 00:37.662
as my opponent, but I printed
out 10,000 "Don't" stickers

00:37.697 --> 00:40.465
and 10,000 question mark
stickers.

00:40.499 --> 00:44.002
That way, if you see a sign
and it says "Recall Knope,"

00:44.036 --> 00:45.954
all you need to do is add
the question mark

00:46.005 --> 00:47.505
and the "Don't,"
and suddenly, it reads,

00:47.523 --> 00:49.624
"Recall Knope?
Don't."

00:49.659 --> 00:50.792
Why don't you
just put the "Don't"

00:50.826 --> 00:52.160
in front of "Recall Knope"?

00:53.763 --> 00:55.564
Yep, that's a much better idea.

00:55.598 --> 00:56.565
Can I have these
question mark stickers?

00:56.616 --> 00:57.615
Why?

00:57.633 --> 00:58.667
I want to put them
on stop signs.

00:58.718 --> 00:59.834
April, no!

00:59.886 --> 01:02.787
[Triumphant music]

01:02.822 --> 01:10.662
